ERROR TIPS

### Errors when using extracting but being too far
 -  Make sure to move to the target entity where you want to extract from before extracting items

### Errors when placing into a tile which is occupied by another entity
- Ensure you can place a entity to a tile before attempting placing

### Errors when moving to a target
- The agent attempts to move to a target with a string index instead of an integer. Ensure that target positions are integers or floats.

### Inserter blocked by transport belt
- The inserter at (40.5, -80.5) is blocked by the transport belt at (39.5, -80.5). Ensure that inserters are not blocked by transport belts.
- The inserters at (6.5, -57.5) and (8.5, -57.5) are blocked. Ensure that inserters are not blocked.

### Inserter already has fuel
- The inserter already has fuel. Avoid inserting fuel into an inserter that already has fuel.

### Not enough resources
- The agent does not have enough iron ore in its inventory. Ensure that the agent has enough iron ore in its inventory before attempting to use it.
- The agent does not have enough wooden chests in its inventory. Ensure that the agent has enough wooden chests in its inventory before attempting to use it.

### Drill has no fuel
- The drill at (41.0, -82.0) has no fuel. Ensure that the drill has fuel before attempting to use it.
